title: Equational Theory
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

An equational theory is a tuple $$(\Sigma, E)$$ of [[Signature]] and equations

Equations in the format $$t=t'$$ s.t. $$t,t' \in \tau(\Sigma)$$ (within the set of [[Term]]s)

For example [[Peano Arithmetic]]: $$E_{PA} = \{ a(x,0)=x, a(x,s(y))=s(a(x,y)) \}$$